{"@context":"http:\/\/iiif.io\/api\/presentation\/3\/context.json","id":"https:\/\/ngagovlittlebdev.prod.acquia-sites.com\/kiosk-story\/919636\/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"en":["What is the hedgehog\u2019s one great trick?"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"en":["Author"]},"value":{"en":["B-Rubenstein@NGA.GOV"]}},{"label":{"en":["Provider"]},"value":{"en":["NGA"]}},{"label":{"en":["artwork-tombstone"]},"value":{"en":["\u003Cp\u003EJoris Hoefnagel\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cem\u003EPlate 48: Guinea Pig and Hedgehogs with Melon and Cobnuts\u003C\/em\u003E\u003Cbr\u003ETerra\u0026nbsp;\u003Cbr\u003Ec.1575\/1590s\u003C\/p\u003E"]}},{"label":{"en":["story-cta"]},"value":{"en":["\u003Cp class=\u0022text-node\u0022 data-pm-slice=\u00221 1 []\u0022\u003EExplore \u003Cem\u003EGuinea Pig and Hedgehogs with Melon and Cobnuts\u003C\/em\u003E\u003C\/p\u003E"]}}],"summary":{"en":["\u003Cp\u003EIn this plate Hoefnagel compares the guinea pig, recently imported into Europe from Peru, and the more familiar hedgehog.\u003C\/p\u003E"]},"requiredStatement":{"label":{"en":["Attribution"]},"value":{"en":["\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECredits\u003C\/strong\u003E\u003Cbr\u003EJoris Hoefnagel, \u003Cem\u003EPlate 48: Guinea Pig and Hedgehogs with Melon and Cobnuts\u003C\/em\u003E, c. 1575\/1590s, watercolor and gold paint on parchment, National Gallery of Art, Washington\u003C\/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ELatin translations and scholarship: Marisa Anne Bass, \u003Cem\u003EInsect Artifice: Nature and Art in the Dutch Revolt\u003C\/em\u003E, Princeton and Oxford: Princeton University Press, 2019.\u003C\/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EImage credit for rolled hedgehog [TBC].\u003C\/p\u003E"]}},"items":[{"id":"https:\/\/ngagovlittlebdev.prod.acquia-sites.com\/node\/919636\/canvases\/1","type":"Canvas","width":5588,"height":4453,"items":[{"id":"https:\/\/ngagovlittlebdev.prod.acquia-sites.com\/node\/919636\/pages\/image\/1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https:\/\/ngagovlittlebdev.prod.acquia-sites.com\/node\/919636\/annotations\/image\/1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","body":{"id":"https:\/\/media.nga.gov\/iiif\/543e1633-a311-4059-bb7b-216d3e778056\/full\/full\/0\/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image\/jpeg","width":5588,"height":4453,"service":[{"id":"https:\/\/media.nga.gov\/iiif\/543e1633-a311-4059-bb7b-216d3e778056","profile":"level2","type":"ImageService2"}]},"target":"https:\/\/ngagovlittlebdev.prod.acquia-sites.com\/node\/919636\/canvases\/1"}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https:\/\/ngagovlittlebdev.prod.acquia-sites.com\/node\/919636\/pages\/text\/1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https:\/\/ngagovlittlebdev.prod.acquia-sites.com\/node\/919636\/pages\/text\/1\/annotation\/0","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"type":"TextualBody","value":"\u003Cp\u003ELatin inscriptions appear on many pages in Joris Hoefnagel\u2019s albums, including this one.\u0026nbsp;\u003C\/p\u003E","language":"en","format":"text\/html"}],"target":"https:\/\/ngagovlittlebdev.prod.acquia-sites.com\/node\/919636\/canvases\/1#xywh=0,0,5588,4453"},{"id":"https:\/\/ngagovlittlebdev.prod.acquia-sites.com\/node\/919636\/pages\/text\/1\/annotation\/1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"type":"TextualBody","value":"\u003Cp\u003EThese inscriptions are bits of poetry, mottos, or proverbs that impart a moral or lesson.\u003C\/p\u003E","language":"en","format":"text\/html","position-hint":"south"}],"target":"https:\/\/ngagovlittlebdev.prod.acquia-sites.com\/node\/919636\/canvases\/1#xywh=911,22,3817,726"},{"id":"https:\/\/ngagovlittlebdev.prod.acquia-sites.com\/node\/919636\/pages\/text\/1\/annotation\/2","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"type":"TextualBody","value":"\u003Cp\u003ETexts at the top and bottom compare a hedgehog with a fox. The bottom inscription reads \u201cThe fox has many tricks, but the hedgehog has one great trick.\u201d\u0026nbsp;\u003C\/p\u003E","language":"en","format":"text\/html","position-hint":"north"}],"target":"https:\/\/ngagovlittlebdev.prod.acquia-sites.com\/node\/919636\/canvases\/1#xywh=813,3708,3536,726"},{"id":"https:\/\/ngagovlittlebdev.prod.acquia-sites.com\/node\/919636\/pages\/text\/1\/annotation\/3","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"type":"TextualBody","value":"\u003Cp\u003EIts trick? Rolling into a ball when it feels threatened.\u0026nbsp;\u003C\/p\u003E","language":"en","format":"text\/html","position-hint":"north"},{"type":"Image","id":"\/sites\/default\/files\/2025-02\/comphedgehog.jpg","format":"image\/jpeg"}],"target":"https:\/\/ngagovlittlebdev.prod.acquia-sites.com\/node\/919636\/canvases\/1#xywh=813,3708,3536,726"},{"id":"https:\/\/ngagovlittlebdev.prod.acquia-sites.com\/node\/919636\/pages\/text\/1\/annotation\/4","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"type":"TextualBody","value":"\u003Cp\u003EIts trick? Rolling into a ball when it feels threatened.\u0026nbsp;\u003C\/p\u003E","language":"en","format":"text\/html","position-hint":"west"}],"target":"https:\/\/ngagovlittlebdev.prod.acquia-sites.com\/node\/919636\/canvases\/1#xywh=3370,2065,1326,859"},{"id":"https:\/\/ngagovlittlebdev.prod.acquia-sites.com\/node\/919636\/pages\/text\/1\/annotation\/5","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"type":"TextualBody","value":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u0026nbsp;plaque above the rolled hedgehog reads \u201cNo strength is anything but an error.\u201d Hoefnagel suggests that the hedgehog\u2019s seemingly weak defense mechanism should be admired.\u003C\/p\u003E","language":"en","format":"text\/html","position-hint":"west"}],"target":"https:\/\/ngagovlittlebdev.prod.acquia-sites.com\/node\/919636\/canvases\/1#xywh=3321,849,1209,1146"},{"id":"https:\/\/ngagovlittlebdev.prod.acquia-sites.com\/node\/919636\/pages\/text\/1\/annotation\/6","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"type":"TextualBody","value":"\u003Cp\u003EOne more inscription is hidden, written in gold below the central hedgehog. It reads: \u201cI wrap myself in virtue.\u201d\u003C\/p\u003E","language":"en","format":"text\/html","position-hint":"south"}],"target":"https:\/\/ngagovlittlebdev.prod.acquia-sites.com\/node\/919636\/canvases\/1#xywh=1880,1760,1607,955"},{"id":"https:\/\/ngagovlittlebdev.prod.acquia-sites.com\/node\/919636\/pages\/text\/1\/annotation\/7","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"type":"TextualBody","value":"\u003Cp\u003EWhat lesson does the hedgehog offer us?\u003C\/p\u003E","language":"en","format":"text\/html"}],"target":"https:\/\/ngagovlittlebdev.prod.acquia-sites.com\/node\/919636\/canvases\/1#xywh=0,0,5588,4453"},{"id":"https:\/\/ngagovlittlebdev.prod.acquia-sites.com\/node\/919636\/pages\/text\/1\/annotation\/8","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"type":"TextualBody","value":"\u003Cp\u003EOne scholar proposed that Hoefnagel wants us to applaud the hedgehog\u2019s self-defense tactic\u2014that its \u201cone great trick\u201d can be useful, even virtuous, when faced with aggression.\u003C\/p\u003E","language":"en","format":"text\/html","position-hint":"north"}],"target":"https:\/\/ngagovlittlebdev.prod.acquia-sites.com\/node\/919636\/canvases\/1#xywh=1880,1760,2838,1179"},{"id":"https:\/\/ngagovlittlebdev.prod.acquia-sites.com\/node\/919636\/pages\/text\/1\/annotation\/9","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"type":"TextualBody","value":"\u003Cp\u003EDo you agree with this? What\u2019s YOUR one great trick?\u003C\/p\u003E","language":"en","format":"text\/html"}],"target":"https:\/\/ngagovlittlebdev.prod.acquia-sites.com\/node\/919636\/canvases\/1#xywh=0,0,5588,4453"}]}]}]}